[size=25] [Center]DanPriest 1.1.0[/Center] [/size]
[size=+2]  [center] Last update: 25th July 2007 [/size]  [/center]


This is only for version 1.1.0 and up! There is pretty big changes in version 1 compared to the beta. So I made this new thread. And it is easier to have a thread with less than 24 pages of replies (for now)

[size=5]Features:[/size]
[size=3]
- All variables is configured through a options menu (no need to edit code)
- Fully configurable pull cast-sequence (with up to seven spells)
- Improved add-control.
- Fully configurable add cast-sequence (with up to seven spell)
- support for trinkets or other items
- Checks for resisted debuffs and recasts
- Should (in theory, never tested) use WillOfTheForsaken if you are undead
- Checks for Power Word: Fortitude before buffing, so you wont waste mana each time you start the glide
- Have a PanicScream option, which will Psychic Scream and heal yourself if hp gets real low.
- Under pull actions it instantly taps the next key if the last spell had casting time, improving the speed of the casting!
- [size +1]Can mount between kills[/size]
- [size +1]Detects if target is a pet of a player, and attacks player instead[/size]
- Have an option to activate active PvP being aggresive against players
- Can use Shadow Protection
[/size]


Howto:
[list=1]
[*]Download the attachment
[*]Unzip it to your classes folder in your glider folder (so all three files is right inside the classes folder)
[*]Start glider (if you havn't already)
[*]Open your glider settings
[*]Press the "Classes" tab
[*]Check DanPriest
[*]Click the "general" tab
[*]On the classes dropdown menu choose DanPriest 1.1.0 (this will of course change when there is new versions)
[*]Press the options button under the class dropdownmenu
[*]Modify the settings for your liking
[*]Open your keys.xml file in your glider folder (if it doesn't exist, you have to open glider -> click options -> click keys -> press save keys)
[*]Add the keys for this class (listed below)
[*]Configure your new keys (you should know how to do this)
  [B]EDIT:[/B] For version 1.0 and up, there are default keys you can use. And in 1.1.0 and up, I have added a keys.xml file that you can use. For editing, I would recommend this program http://vforums.mmoglider.com/showthread.php?t=75086
[*]Open the glider options once again, and press the keys tab
[*]Press Load Keys
[*]Make sure your keys is correct ingame too
[*]Start to glide
[*]Go back here and post you result, questions, bugs and suggestions
[/list]

As of eating and bandaging, I'm just using the internal code, and I think that would be find, I see no need to do it myself. Just go to options - limits and adjust the values there

[B]It is really important that you do not have any special spell on the Common.CooldownProbe (which is by default key 2 on the combat bar) as my class often look at that key to determine if global cooldown is done, if you have a spell with no global cooldown or a spell with a long cooldown there (imagine a 5min cooldown spell...) please edit the Common.CooldowProbe to another key, or place a better spell on combat bar, button 2[/B]





